# Generated documentation-graph artifacts (tools/doc-graph/generate.mjs).
#
# These are committed for GitHub-navigability but are machine-generated and
# re-render heavily on every structure-changing regeneration — the SVG is a
# full dot re-layout, and the JSON manifest's per-node commit-distance fields
# are HEAD-relative, so they shift on essentially every commit. Left unmarked,
# a routine doc change produces a ~10k-line diff that floods review, skews the
# repo's language stats, inflates the PR +/- line count (misleading, and the
# churn shape that trips scraper / abuse heuristics).
#
# `linguist-generated=true` → collapse in diffs + exclude from language stats.
# `-diff` on the two large machine-rendered files → GitHub treats them as
# binary ("not shown"), so their re-render neither floods review nor counts
# toward the +/- total. The small human-readable index + validator report stay
# diffable (you DO want to see staleness-table / dangling-ref changes).
#
# The manifest (docs/doc-graph.json) remains the source of truth — `--check`
# reads it; suppressing its DISPLAY does not weaken the freshness gate. See
# ADR-0005 (Alternative C, partly adopted) and the umbrella CLAUDE.md
# "Documentation is part of the work" doc-graph audit item.
# docs/doc-graph.svg removed 2026-06-01 — it is now rendered locally and
# .gitignore'd, not committed (`-diff` never decounted it on GitHub anyway).
docs/doc-graph.json         linguist-generated=true -diff
docs/doc-graph.md           linguist-generated=true
docs/doc-graph-report.md    linguist-generated=true
